Definition
-----------

*proof-by-contradiction-1* is the :ref:`inference-rule<inference_rule_math_concept>`:

.. math::

    \left( \mathcal{H} \; \text{assume} \; \neg \mathbf{P}, \mathit{Inc}\left(\mathcal{H}\right)  \right) \vdash \mathbf{P}

Where:

  * :math:`\mathcal{H}` is an :ref:`hypothesis<hypothesis_math_concept>`
  * :math:`\mathbf{P}` is a propositional :ref:`formula<formula_math_concept>`
  * :math:`\mathit{Inc}` is the inconsistency function